06072c5dfd2cc0d8.voiceContent: Never mind, haha. I just had the best idea...

0e05b879830fff60.voiceContent: My father and brother are always ready to give me another earful...

0ff3c0cbe014c414.voiceContent: *sigh* Oh, how I would love to take up the sword with you... pursuing justice throughout the land!

1483ecdd8d7a5876.voiceContent: Tell me, what have you been doing recently?

1dfc509f7510aa1e.voiceContent: I was just wondering whether you might appear.

23b701d79468000e.voiceContent: Oh...! Don't forget our arrangement. If you witness an injustice on the road, please fetch me.

26965b7c484f8bbe.voiceContent: Ahem... If I may so ask, where do you usually collect your literature? Perhaps you could share a tip or two with a friend, my liege...?

3a1a6dda26772410.voiceContent: Y—You... Ahem... I assume you're familiar with the proverb Be it but three moons from the start, he who returns is not he that departs.

403a6eb7cf109d2f.voiceContent: Just... Don't expect to win too easily.

4830bba12ac79de3.voiceContent: So... A—Anyway, I won't bore you. Feel free to peruse it at your own pace.

587d161f08a3acff.voiceContent: And yet here I am, perceiving it with my own senses.

5d5d33f87c6b6524.voiceContent: I'll make sure to highlight any particularly enthralling passages I encounter and share them with you later.

63875cbca99229c2.voiceContent: Why don't we have ourselves a little contest? First to a hundred chivalrous acts wins!

6a2eced40ea7fddf.voiceContent: Magnificent! Acts of pure chivalry by the sound of it.

70913a437191675f.voiceContent: Hehe... A pity that it will have to wait until some point in the future. But if we're talking about the here and now... Ooh! I got it...

7c417d72c97d9e47.voiceContent: All of these rare books... many of them can hardly be found at Wanwen Bookhouse, or even in all of Liyue.

81621ae656e374d9.voiceContent: But of course! It's always a pleasure to talk with you.

8a48f9caed12f8ee.voiceContent: Oh! Well, if you have the time, I'd like to get your critique on... on this short story I wrote.

8ab3e99741212158.voiceContent: In any case, you are a part of this story.

8ba9b5c90dd88f4c.voiceContent: Wow, your wits are a lot sharper these days. I must be rubbing off on you...

8c1a287e5091306c.voiceContent: This place captures the atmosphere, yet avoids such disturbances and clamor as are common to the city.

99348837203dfdf8.voiceContent: Even if it were to exist solely upon the page, this teapot realm would not fail to inspire.

9a9809a832e4809a.voiceContent: Okay okay, geez... We know each other pretty well by now, no need to get all sappy.

9d93246d40e4b63a.voiceContent: A stroll here will certainly serve as inspiration for my writing!

bbd512727b21c8e1.voiceContent: But please... Don't let anyone else hear you talking about it...

bccf4eb32dd2558b.voiceContent: There are no restrictions on the nature of the act or the beneficiary. But you need to keep a tally. Once the act is completed, it should be verified by the other party.

cd86cb27812619c1.voiceContent: Oh, hehe — uh... don't mind me.

f53df77cb585c7df.voiceContent: That was then... and this is now...

f66e5663c4c87d03.voiceContent: Your design for this street is most exquisite.

f80327b0642d6e9d.voiceContent: So remember, I want your honest opinion. That way, the sequel will be even better...

fd1824052f8e8362.voiceContent: I wouldn't dream of neglecting any of that!

fe420816da107334.voiceContent: Well... I can read at my leisure here, for hours on end, without any fear of interruption. Ahh... the perfect getaway...

042e35c9feb9d2c3.voiceContent: In her capacity as the Tianquan, I am obliged to respect her. Otherwise, it could create issues for my father and brother. On a personal level? Let me think... I think I will go with no comment. I shan't speak ill of others.

170003ae6f6d2414.voiceContent: Morning! The morn hours are precious. Spend them on that which matters to you.

178d0b9b61b6f180.voiceContent: Had I no moral compass, my efforts would have been misguided. Doomed to grasp at shadows while missing the substance, I would have become a philistine that seeks only violence.

1d777b60cb787d04.voiceContent: Are you keeping well, my liege? If you have no other matters to attend to, might I recommend a trip to the Wanwen Bookhouse?

20e949bbeb2fef4b.voiceContent: Have you thought of a countermeasure yet?

21db1faa9c504cb9.voiceContent: I always have to put on an act around other people, because they see me only as the second son of the Feiyun Commerce Guild. It's a relief that I can just be myself around you. I think it's because you don't see me in the same way.

221275cd95b0a6a5.voiceContent: Hey, that's a little too far!

2dfbe3873f3bad24.voiceContent: If my calculations are correct, Wanwen Bookhouse is due to receive a batch of new releases today. Might we add a small detour to our adventure?

3f79d2265eb885c0.voiceContent: I used to like rabbits, but I'm more a fan of stags now. To me, the saying May my final stand be a monument to chivalry is about abandoning worldly possessions and reaching enlightenment. But the stag's final resting place represents the hope for life anew. Oh, how I'd love to see it again.

40845606f0ce603c.voiceContent: I need only sample this delight but once for its aroma to remain forever in my memory.

457678b1d356c194.voiceContent: When you first spot Xiangling out and about, the first thing you should do is check the look on her face. Especially when she's just coming back from collecting new ingredients — the more excited she looks, the more dangerous it is to approach. Because if she sees you, she'll force you to taste-test her latest concoction... I usually get Chongyun to handle these situations, hehe...

4e077c235996e498.voiceContent: According to historical records, Tiancheng's stone bridge was formed by a fallen rock spear thrown by the Geo Archon Morax in battle. If you walk along the bridge on your birthday and throw some Mora into the sea from both sides, you will be blessed in the coming year... Your birthday only comes once a year, so be quick about it if you wanna go... I'm not kidding, it's true! Go try it and you'll see!

4f5e676835955eca.voiceContent: I am most grateful for your company on my journey. I am proud of my achievements, both in the martial arts and in championing the cause so dear to my heart. ...Ah, I guess there's no need to euphemize any longer. Chivalry! That is the cause that inspires me, and that I seek to champion. Why should I shy away from it? I am sure my father and brother are under no illusion as to what I stand for by now. ...But of course, I still need to be somewhat discreet in the way I go about my business.

5230bbf0b5609f4e.voiceContent: I couldn't possibly. But please, you eat your fill. I insist.

598a5f79afbe6e38.voiceContent: I hope we find long-lost ancient literature.

5d71661d2016dca5.voiceContent: There aren't many records on matters concerning Visions, but I do have a passage dedicated to the topic in my collection of ancient texts. I can lend it to you if you want.

5f8bb18e3541a9af.voiceContent: I never embark on a journey without a good book to accompany me.

611c9e5f983efcb4.voiceContent: I can no longer hold back.

63c964e2ad1f10ef.voiceContent: Shall I lend you a book with some strategy tips?

643b74de08b592d7.voiceContent: Good, the rain has stopped. Any longer and my books would have gotten wet.

684eca52c39b332f.voiceContent: I have taught you... everything... I know...

6867f122d07f5f87.voiceContent: I would say we are book buddies. Huh? Combat? Guhua Clan? Comrades in arms? ...What on earth are you talking about? I told you that's our little secret!

6fd8f430687772df.voiceContent: Very well. I was just reading about this game. It seems straightforward enough.

709ee591e5c96581.voiceContent: There is a cause that I seek to champion, yet few in Liyue share my aspiration. This I have known for a long time, for it is a path I have walked for many years.

710ad75194f575b2.voiceContent: Your schedule is free today? Wonderful. I am ready to leave whenever you are. ...My book? Oh, never mind that! I can always pick up where I left off when I get back. But those in distress who need our assistance cannot afford to wait.

7bef46ddef63accc.voiceContent: Where does Xinyan perform? Anywhere from Chihu Rock to Yujing Terrace — no spot is untouched by her disruptive presence... A quiet day when I can curl up with a good book is a rare treasure indeed.

80c0a02b66042a04.voiceContent: Ah yes, the young lady who is now the Master of the Wangsheng Funeral Parlor. If you're asking what I think about her as a person... Well, there are all sorts of rumors about the way she works. But I think if you really want to understand someone, you need to find out what they are really after.

817bf39928f4fe18.voiceContent: Evidently, my hobby is reading. I'll read anything and everything. ...What's that mischievous grin for? Oh. That's between the two of us, okay? It's not appropriate to discuss it out loud. There's no point in bringing it up anyway.

838dea47e6d56988.voiceContent: I've thought of all the illustrations I want for each major event in the next three volumes! I should write my thoughts down before I forget them, and send them to Mr. Kreideprinz...

8627408de4411aae.voiceContent: What say you we snatch a few fireflies and read in the light they give? Hehe... Hey, I'm joking. Seriously, don't, it's bad for your eyesight.

870c4042b0b2e9d9.voiceContent: Huh!? But I went by the book...

8da797936cee80c4.voiceContent: Have you heard the expression same person, different face? Ms. Yelan gives me precisely this feeling. When she came to visit my family, my father and brother treated her with respect, and she was pleasant and polite in return. She seemed like a kind and mature young lady to me. But when I saw her elsewhere, she gave a completely different impression.

924a957b45283689.voiceContent: You feel inspired, you say? You want to write a martial arts detective novel based on our adventures together? And you want to call it the Chronicles of Wanwen? Hahaha... It's a good idea, it really is. But I'll have to decline, I'm sorry. Yes, really...

9a244a148c87ed86.voiceContent: I find that Miss Shenhe seems to look at me somewhat fiercely, so I daren't approach her lightly. Bizarre, did I inadvertently upset her? Or maybe... upset someone close to her?

a7b87ab90be9b731.voiceContent: Only when it snows like this would I prefer to be at home than in a book store. For there is a well-stocked fireplace at home, while there is no fire allowed in book stores.

a7dc68099a8fc27d.voiceContent: I have great respect for Lady Beidou. I just wish she wouldn't call me kid and ruffle my hair each time she sees me.

a8a9caf177e7ae92.voiceContent: Come. I have devised a plan.

aa91747e4e5bbfa6.voiceContent: You will find me in the same place as ever tomorrow. So I'll see you then. Unless you manage to get lost on the way.

ae90c3c06293635d.voiceContent: What annoys me? Hmm... Well, one day my brother will inherit the family business. What will happen to me then? I fear my current carefree existence would... Oh — no no no, it's not about my status or anything like that. I don't care for that kind of thing. I just think my brother is something of a simpleton and I would probably end up having to do most of his job for him...

aff01d7efc0ad6b5.voiceContent: Oh my goodness... Oh my gosh... Wow— Huh? All will be revealed in the next volume? Aw, drat...

b3364a62c3ce68ac.voiceContent: When Yun Jin drinks a beverage she is fond of, she will be inspired to write a new play. So, I keep a jar of tea leaves under my bed at all times, ready to deliver to her on the day that her inspiration dries up. This way, I shall never run out of heroic tales to listen to!

b8928a08cdfd3e1f.voiceContent: May this day of your birth be filled with much mirth!

ba64d8561c7fa305.voiceContent: May my final stand be a monument to chivalry.

bc0636d4239d9afe.voiceContent: Xingqiu at your service, my liege! I humbly trust that even one such as I, a mere bookworm, may yet prove to be of some utility under your wise leadership. Nice, I don't often get a chance to speak with such formality. It felt pretty good!

be5e4ae72fd0dc03.voiceContent: I like baked goods and Yue-style seafood. Probably because I'm used to quite a bland diet at home.

c09cc22a7e847e5c.voiceContent: Impressive, you made some amazing plays there.

c0cc7982ac6394e7.voiceContent: Were it not for my capability, the cause that so inspires me would remain confined to the pages that extol its virtues.

c69cfefecf9807c0.voiceContent: Great weather for practicing martial arts, but perfect weather for reading. Hey, what's that ridiculous look for? You look as if you're trying to decipher some strange text written on my forehead.

c741c6389a236f2a.voiceContent: Must-see places in Liyue? That's a tough question. Hmm... The place I would miss the most if it disappeared would be the Wanwen Bookhouse, first and foremost. The Guhua Sect would be in the top ten, too.

c88ec33b3c74bbee.voiceContent: My family makes ornate umbrellas that block neither rain nor shine. Their sole purpose is for decoration upon a wall.

c9551e3afe7eb168.voiceContent: I need only sample this delight but once for its aroma to remain forever in my memory.

d2b3850b1dfdb678.voiceContent: Oh, done already? I still have so many more decks I want to try.

d53320b1dd78b2a4.voiceContent: Ah, dear Chongyun. Though he understands me quite well, one has to exercise caution when teaming up with him to go on a quest. He is making good progress in the martial arts, but I would say he hasn't quite internalized the chivalric code yet... He needs more practice. Especially at eating spicy food...

d5eafbe665394835.voiceContent: I've always thought there is more to Qiqi than meets the eye. But it's impossible to have a conversation with her when Baizhu's around. Hmm... We could wait till Baizhu makes a home call to one of his other patients and corner her...

d73dda82e2b8cdc6.voiceContent: We should become sworn siblings, let's go to the altar at Jueyun Karst. Nope, no ifs, no buts, you know too much about me! You know the real me, the one I normally have to hide. I simply can't let you go until you promise me you will go through with it!

da684f9675be55c6.voiceContent: Now this is what I call, a moment of solitude.

def94a533db03e4d.voiceContent: I hate carrots. When I was young, my mother would mash them up into... Ugh, I can't go on. Just thinking about it makes me feel sick...

e1c7516c40015870.voiceContent: I am uninclined to eat a heavy meal this luncheon, but instead indulge in some baked treats. As long as I eat in the study, my father and brother never have to know! Oh, you want to join me? Well... As long as you don't get crumbs on the books, I suppose it's fine.

e20c02eaf07ee506.voiceContent: Over-reliance on book knowledge is worse than no book knowledge at all...

e47bfb824d17b3c8.voiceContent: A weaver of verses who draws from an ocean of expression... That's the reputation I aspire to. But you're the only person I can share that with. I am actually writing a novel... but I can't let you see it. Not yet. The time will come, though... You'll be able to read it when it's on sale in book stores all over Liyue.

eed98d3ee0a5e036.voiceContent: With cooking skills as good as yours, it'd be a waste not to open a restaurant, wouldn't you agree?

efde706000303274.voiceContent: I've come to an epiphany based on some things I've been reading — ultimately, the arts of both the polearm and the sword are just the art of hand-eye coordination. Ugh, it's a little difficult to explain... If you want to know more, come with me to Wangshan Hall. But first, you have to promise me you won't laugh.

f0d98927fdec09c4.voiceContent: Let me weave you a verse.

f2fe494951c34bfb.voiceContent: You ask why I enjoy reading in solitude? ...Studiousness can hardly be considered a bad habit. There's not much more to it than that. Really.

f50163a8c0dc96e8.voiceContent: 'Twas on a deserted moonlit night that the hero approached the vile dragon's limpid lair...

f63522b59467bbfb.voiceContent: It all comes down to luck in the end, and you know I'm not one to cheat. Hehe, so bring it on...

f93e16fd38b84a28.voiceContent: Hmm... Are you sure you don't want me to play with a handicap?

fb166797c1250ff2.voiceContent: I couldn't possibly. But please, you eat your fill. I insist.

fe02388b104d3e42.voiceContent: With cooking skills as good as yours, it'd be a waste not to open a restaurant, wouldn't you agree?

ff5ef9e92310d9d6.voiceContent: My father and brother entertained that gentleman as a guest once. From the way they were acting, he must be a very high-profile figure indeed. I also heard that he directs funerals for the adepti, so he must surely have great depth to his character. We should do some digging and see what we can find out about him!
